00:07:03.570 --> 00:07:06.660
that at least I hadn't
heard of until recently,

00:07:06.660 --> 00:07:09.620
which is the concept of salutogenesis.

00:07:09.620 --> 00:07:12.810
Many of us are familiar with
the concept of pathogenesis,

00:07:12.810 --> 00:07:14.970
the idea that there are
all these scary diseases

00:07:14.970 --> 00:07:18.070
like dementia and heart
disease and stroke,

00:07:18.070 --> 00:07:19.850
and all these things that await us

00:07:19.850 --> 00:07:21.520
if we don't take good care of ourselves

00:07:21.520 --> 00:07:24.340
and that might await us even if we do,

00:07:24.340 --> 00:07:26.341
that's the pathogenic model,

00:07:26.341 --> 00:07:28.140
salutogenesis is something I learned about

00:07:28.140 --> 00:07:30.270
from one of my Stanford
Medicine colleagues,

00:07:30.270 --> 00:07:31.660
which is a different orientation

00:07:31.660 --> 00:07:32.790
toward health and well-being

00:07:32.790 --> 00:07:35.540
where you're taking on
particular behaviors,

00:07:35.540 --> 00:07:37.420
you're taking on a particular stance

00:07:37.420 --> 00:07:40.820
towards nutrition and exercise,
supplementation, et cetera,

00:07:40.820 --> 00:07:44.340
in order to promote well-being
above where you would be

00:07:44.340 --> 00:07:46.323
if you were not doing those behaviors.

00:07:46.323 --> 00:07:48.510
Now, if you think about
it, these two things,

00:07:48.510 --> 00:07:50.860
salutogenesis and the pathogenic model,

00:07:50.860 --> 00:07:53.220
are really two sides of the same coin,

00:07:53.220 --> 00:07:54.720
but I'll just give an example

00:07:54.720 --> 00:07:57.610
of how this might affect
you in a real way.

00:07:57.610 --> 00:08:01.240
If you like exercise because
it feels good, great,

00:08:01.240 --> 00:08:04.780
but many people exercise, or
eat well, for that matter,

00:08:04.780 --> 00:08:08.250
in order to avoid heart
disease or to avoid dementia,

00:08:08.250 --> 00:08:12.440
to avoid negative changes
in body composition,

00:08:12.440 --> 00:08:14.000
and while that's powerful

00:08:14.000 --> 00:08:15.980
and certainly is the case that exercise

00:08:15.980 --> 00:08:18.140
will help you move away
from all those things,

00:08:18.140 --> 00:08:19.950
the salutogenesis model differs

00:08:19.950 --> 00:08:22.790
in that it involves a
mindset and an orientation

00:08:22.790 --> 00:08:25.340
towards doing those things
in order to feels good,

00:08:25.340 --> 00:08:27.280
in order to enhance your level of energy,

00:08:27.280 --> 00:08:29.400
in order to improve endocrine function

00:08:29.400 --> 00:08:30.950
and metabolic function,

00:08:30.950 --> 00:08:33.830
so it's really part of
the pathogenic model,

00:08:33.830 --> 00:08:36.460
and yet, salutogenesis is
really more of a mindset

00:08:36.460 --> 00:08:38.770
toward why you would do
these particular behaviors,

00:08:38.770 --> 00:08:40.410
and really, the most powerful mindset

00:08:40.410 --> 00:08:42.520
is going to be one where you are thinking

00:08:42.520 --> 00:08:43.860
about the pathogenic model,

00:08:43.860 --> 00:08:46.680
doing things so that you
don't end up sick, et cetera,

00:08:46.680 --> 00:08:48.370
and to move away from sickness,

00:08:48.370 --> 00:08:51.270
as well as the salutogenic
model where you're doing things

00:08:51.270 --> 00:08:53.760
in order to move towards
health and well-being.

00:08:53.760 --> 00:08:55.730
We think of health and wellness nowadays,

00:08:55.730 --> 00:08:58.700
or the wellness community
or wellness practices,

00:08:58.700 --> 00:09:00.340
and in many ways,

00:09:00.340 --> 00:09:02.940
